content: These games were my favorite growing up. I remember spending all day and night on my Windows '95 playing. Very clever humor. Entertaining, funny story lines. Simple point n click game that feels like a puzzel. I play on my chromebook and have no issues.
Just like when I was a kid! This was amazing if your looking for some good memories pay the $5!

Wonderful, only problem I had was that it would freeze if I accidentally pressed to check my inventory twice in a row. Other than that everything was smooth. And even if I did freeze, the auto save was, "in there like swimwear" so I just had to close and reopen to the same spot no problem!

Yes! This game worked amazingly! I lived for these games, so happy when they made them for mobile. The game worked perfectly for me, not sure what the problems everyone else was having. It didn't have a single glitch or running issues for me. I have an older android, so maybe that's why? Either way, very nice.
Great game just some times there is no sound please fixðŸ˜­
It was so glitchy that I couldn't play. I couldn't get to his spy gadgets without the game freezing! ðŸ˜¡

The Game is a masterpiece of clever humor and great level design. The port of this game to mobile honestly feels sloppy. It crashes several times every time I play it. Luckily it has a good autosave feature so it doesn't set me too far back when it does crash.

I enjoyed playing this game as a kid and still enjoy playing this game as an adult! So much nostalgia! For the people who are having issues playing the game, maybe your phone couldn't support playing the game or you have received the update yet.
I have saved milk, thank goodness. XD The app is great fun and I'll eventually get the other two, hopefully they'll add even more to the Play Store at some point. UwU
Exactly like the old PC version.

Plays well despite numerous crashes. -1 star for crash frequency. It is a quick fix to clear the cache and reboot the game. Does not lose where you are after reboot. Otherwise it's a fun nostalgic game that plays like the original. It feels like the go fish games got harder but that might just be my bad luck.
Glitchy and very short game
I love this game; and even more the subject, milk makes pajama sam's favorite food: CHEESE!

I'm so happy to play my favorite childhood game again! I played this when I was a child! Love the idea of having my childhood game on my phone! :)
Very happy to be able to play one of my childhood games again only now on mobile!
it was okay, i use to play this when i was younger. wish it was free again, cause it isn't worth $7.99
this game lags a lot. I cant hear half of the conversations. not worth the $5!

classic, i love it.

Love this game even as an adult it brings back memories of my childhood memories with my grandma.

The game sounds sped up. As for go fish, I'll always have 3 of multiple cards and never draw the 4th. He will and then will get all 3 of mine. When I draw a card he has, its like he knows and then asks for that card right away. He'll end up with 5 or 6 suits and I'm lucky if I get 1.
The game is great it's just the voices are super high pitched. The other games are perfect just this one is high pitched
I have a LG G4 and it doesn't have sound I seen somwhere else it didn't have sound on the LG V10 either please fix!
Has no sound on lg v10. Love this game on pc but can't play it without any sound
One of the variables for the game doesn't work the app shuts down every time I try to play it (one without the racoon guy), but for the other one the app works fine. Please fix.
Rage

Into an app, I mean. Loved to play it on my PC way back. And I love being able to switch between subtitles or none, as English is not my native tongue. Thanks, and I'll definitely get the other games, too! Just fix the voices, please, they really are too high-pitched and too fast at times.

It's pretty great replaying this game over just to see how much you can remember from way back when, however, the sounds are high pitched. It's not all that horrible, especially if you're a first time player, but for nostalgia sake, comparing it to a youtube video from the pc version, it's very weird sounding.
The childhood memories come flooding back... Wow... just, wow...

Loved the game, brought in a sense of nostalgia from  Childhood the only issue I have is the voices sound higher pitched like it's been sped up. Hoping that can be fixed so it sounds more fluid and normal. Other than that perfect game.
Cool game
I'm sad because I lived this game as a kid but it kept glitching during play making my phone freeze :(

I emailed humongous entertainment and they told me to uninstall and reinstall the game to fix the bugs, but that makes you start over. Unplayable.
